\n<Detective>Good work. I heard that a severe madman was
found in this park...
\n<Detective>Ah, Detective. It was really tough...

\n<Detective>Even though it's daytime, these madmen were...
engaging in an orgy. Right in the middle of the
park.
Actor03
\n<Detective>...What? Orgy...?

\n<Detective>And it was between men. I don't have any intention
of judging people's sexual preferences, but it's a
crime in a public place, you know.

\n<Detective>We restrained and apprehended them with the help
of a report when they were about to attack a
passing woman...

\n<Detective>Their strength was incredible... We even
considered mobilizing the riot police at one
point. They were truly madmen.
Actor03

\n<Detective>...It's hard to believe that it was simply a
matter of losing control over their sexual
impulses without any underlying reason.

\n<Detective>Regardless of the cause, if we don't resolve this
quickly, it seems that this town will soon become
a ghost town.

\n<Grandma>There was a single mother and her daughter, but
the mother was a terrible person.

\n<Grandma>She would leave her daughter alone and go around
playing with different men every day.

\n<Grandma>Besides, we used to hear shouting every day, and
they were a well-known family in the neighborhood,
but we haven't seen them recently.

\n<Grandma>She wasn't cheerful, but she was a cute girl. I
hope that child is safe...
\n<Fat man>Huh...huh...he's not here today either...

\n<Fat man>Huh...huh...this is strange...he was supposed to
be lurking around here...it was written on the
board...!

\n<Fat man>I... I'll definitely find you... Little Angel...
Aria-chan!!
\n<Grandfather>Oh, you're not coming today either, Miss Hat.

\n<Grandfather>Do you know? There's a little girl wearing a baggy
white coat who often sits alone on that bench over
there.

\n<Grandfather>She's a quiet child, and since she doesn't talk
much, I don't really know what happened, but she
looks pitiful, thin and unfortunate.

\n<Grandfather>I was hoping you could give her some food and keep
this old man company...
\n<Grandfather>I see, maybe she found another place to be.
